-- Tofas shares rise after announces new model investment plans 
-- 
-- Thu Nov 06, 2014 02:44AM EST
-- None



ISTANBUL, Nov 6 (Reuters) - Shares in automaker Tofas, owned by Turkey's Koc Holding <KCHOL.IS> and Italy's Fiat <FCHA.MI>, rose 2.55 percent after it announced $1 billion investment plans to produce new models.

